* Re: CATER #154483 for 12G-QF1 topoff interlock
text: Replaced original bitbus controller, but was unable to resolve the resistance interlock problem by recalibrating the output voltage V/V setting. Replaced the bitbus controller with a second unit and was successful in correcting the resistance interlock after recalibration of the output voltage V/V parameter. Original bitbus unit (Out) = PCD09022 First bitbus unit that was unsuccessful, then removed = PCD09053 Final bitbus unit (In) = PCD09003 AN/ML

* Re: CATER #154483 for 12G-QF1 topoff interlock
text: Some facts about magnet 12G-QF1 that caused topoff interlock fault: 1. Voltage was increased 2V this week to 73.75V compared to last month of 71.7V. 2. Resistance was up to 0.984 ohm compared to last month of 0.956 ohm. 3. Current is stabled at 75.02A throughout from last month to this week. 4. Voltage coefficient is still the same from last time, nothing change at 20.28 5. Thermal temp checking revealed nothing abnormal at 12G-QF1 supply rack. 6. Next step is to replace bitbus controller for 12G-QF1. After 2 replacements, lots of measurements, voltage co-efficiency calibrations, we finally got the voltage and resistance value close to last monthâs value. That will fix the topoff interlock fault and SPEAR ring can be operated again.

title: Shift summary: Thursday swing
text: SUMMARY: 12G-QF1 resistance fault was resolved early in the shift, then accelerator physics programs began. No problems. INJECTOR: Up when needed for SPEAR fills. There was over 300mV Q, with fill rate of 48mA/minute. SPEAR: The team working on 12G-QF1 resolved the issue by 5pm. SPEAR was standardized and filled to 100mA to verify operation, then low-current AP programs were performed (LOCO, orbit interlock, QMS). QMS is expected to finish shortly after midnight, at which time SPEAR will be filled to 500mA, beamlines will be opened, and topoff will be enabled.
